                <h1>Understanding Juvenile Criminal Records: What You Need to Know</h1>
                <p>Juvenile criminal records serve as a record of offenses committed by minors. These records can impact future opportunities, including education and employment. Understanding how to seal or expunge these records is crucial for affected individuals, as it can help mitigate long-term consequences and promote a second chance at life.</p>
